quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  4,142,"The hypocrites would deceive God, but He will deceive them! When they stand up for prayer, they stand carelessly, to be seen of men, and they remember God but little"
  4,143,Wavering between the one and the other - belonging neither to these nor those! and by no means shalt thou find a path for him whom God misleadeth
  4,144,O believers! take not infidels for friends rather than believers. Would ye furnish God with clear right to punish you
  4,145,"Verily the hypocrites shall be in the lowest abyss of the fire: and, by no means shalt thou find a helper for them"
  4,146,"Save for those who turn and amend, and lay fast hold on God, and approve the sincerity of their religion to God; these shall be numbered with the faithful, and God will at last bestow on the faithful a great reward"
  4,147,"Why should God inflict a chastisement upon you, if ye are grateful, and believe? God is Grateful, Wise"
  4,148,"God loveth not that evil be matter of public talk, unless any one hath been wronged: God it is who Heareth, Knoweth"
  4,149,"Whether ye publish what is good, or conceal it, or pardon evil, verily God is Pardoning, Powerful"
  4,150,"Of a truth they who believe not on God and his Apostles, and seek to separate God from his Apostles, and say, \"Some we believe, and some we believe not,\" and desire to take a middle way"
  4,151,These! they are veritable infidels! and for the infidels have we prepared a shameful punishment
  4,152,"And they who believe on God and his Apostles, and make no difference between them these! we will bestow on them their reward at last. God is Gracious, Merciful"